<subSubSection id="C33D1CE3FFA4FF8FFF54FEE86DF81BBD" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B984F68FFA4FF8FFF54FEE86B4B1D0B" blockId="6.[151,1437,356,1310]" pageId="6" pageNumber="24">
Subshrub to ca. 
<quantity id="4CDFE28DFFA4FF8FFE97FEE86ECA1E13" box="[340,412,356,382]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" unit="cm" value="30.0">30 cm</quantity>
tall. Completely glabrous. Leaves: stipules linear, 2–2.5 × ca. 
<quantity id="4CDFE28DFFA4FF8FFBB4FEE86B831E13" box="[1143,1237,356,382]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="0.4">0.4 mm</quantity>
, often persistent; petiole 
<quantity id="4CDFE28DFFA4FF8FFF30FE066E1F1EC9" box="[243,329,394,420]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
long; blade broadly elliptic to suborbicular, 16 × 
<quantity id="4CDFE28DFFA4FF8FFC7CFE066B4E1EC9" box="[959,1048,394,420]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="12.0">12 mm</quantity>
, base obtuse, margin shallowly crenate-serrate, apex rounded to subacute, slightly glaucous below, without marginal glands, side veins in 5–6 pairs. Staminate inflorescence 
<quantity id="4CDFE28DFFA4FF8FFDD2FE546D231E9F" box="[529,629,472,498]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="6.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="6.0">6–7 mm</quantity>
long; bracts c. 
<quantity id="4CDFE28DFFA4FF8FFCF5FE546CF41E9F" box="[822,930,472,498]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="0.25">0.25 mm</quantity>
long, with a pair of stipitate disc-shaped glands ca. 
<quantity id="4CDFE28DFFA4FF8FFED4FE726ED71D75" box="[279,385,510,536]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="0.15">0.15 mm</quantity>
in diam.; staminate flowers three per bract, their pedicel ca. 
<quantity id="4CDFE28DFFA4FF8FFB9FFE726BEE1D75" box="[1116,1208,510,536]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="0.2">0.2 mm</quantity>
long, the calyx ca. 
<quantity id="4CDFE28DFFA4FF8FFF54FDA96FA91D52" box="[151,255,549,575]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="0.12">0.12 mm</quantity>
long. Pistillate flowers not seen. Fruits: pedicel ca. 
<quantity id="4CDFE28DFFA4FF8FFC9CFDA96CEF1D52" box="[863,953,549,575]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.3 mm</quantity>
long; capsule ellipsoid, sulcate, ca. 3.2 × 
<quantity id="4CDFE28DFFA4FF8FFF54FDC06FA51D0B" box="[151,243,588,614]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="3.2">3.2 mm</quantity>
, smooth, with rows of multiple short appendages to ca. 
<quantity id="4CDFE28DFFA4FF8FFC42FDC06C8C1D0B" box="[897,986,588,614]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="0.7">0.7 mm</quantity>
long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B984F68FFA4FF8FFF05FDFE6D641C4A" blockId="6.[151,1437,356,1310]" pageId="6" pageNumber="24">
This species had been included by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB63299FFA4FF8FFDA3FDFE6C291DE1" author="Pax, F. &amp; Hoffmann, K." box="[608,895,626,652]" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" pagination="52" refId="ref4728" refString="Pax, F. &amp; Hoffmann, K. (1912) Euphorbiaceae-Hippomaneae. In: Engler, A. (ed.), Das Pflanzenreich IV, 147, V (Heft 52). Engelmann, Leipzig." type="book chapter" year="1912">Pax &amp; Hoffmann (1912)</bibRefCitation>
in their section 
<taxonomicName id="4C2734EBFFA4FF8FFBFEFDFE6D491DDE" authority="(F. Muller 1857: 17) Pax &amp; Hoffmann (1912: 114)" authorityName="Pax &amp; Hoffmann" authorityPageNumber="114" authorityYear="1912" baseAuthorityName="F. Muller" baseAuthorityPageNumber="17" baseAuthorityYear="1857" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Elachocroton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B953937AFFA4FF8FFBFEFDFE6B8A1DE6" box="[1085,1244,626,651]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="24">Elachocroton</emphasis>
(F. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB63299FFA4FF8FFB3CFDFE6FE31DDE" author="Muller, F." pageId="6" pageNumber="24" pagination="14 - 24" refId="ref4620" refString="Muller, F. (1857). Nova genera et species aliquot rariores in plagis Australiae intratropicis nuperrime detecta. Hooker's journal of botany and Kew Garden miscellany 9: 14 - 24." type="journal article" year="1857">Müller 1857: 17</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB63299FFA4FF8FFF06FD156D491DDE" author="Pax, F. &amp; Hoffmann, K." box="[197,543,665,691]" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" pagination="52" refId="ref4728" refString="Pax, F. &amp; Hoffmann, K. (1912) Euphorbiaceae-Hippomaneae. In: Engler, A. (ed.), Das Pflanzenreich IV, 147, V (Heft 52). Engelmann, Leipzig." type="book chapter" year="1912">Pax &amp; Hoffmann (1912: 114)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which is now part of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2734EBFFA4FF8FFCE3FD156CEB1DDF" authorityName="Jussieu" authorityYear="1824" box="[800,957,665,690]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Microstachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B953937AFFA4FF8FFCE3FD156CEB1DDF" box="[800,957,665,690]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="24">Microstachys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB63299FFA4FF8FFC08FD156B361DDE" author="Esser, H. - J." box="[971,1120,665,691]" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" pagination="955 - 960" refId="ref4280" refString="Esser, H. - J. (1998) New combinations in Microstachys (Euphorbiaceae). Kew Bulletin 53: 955 - 960." type="journal article" year="1998">Esser (1998)</bibRefCitation>
suggested that it might not belong to 
<taxonomicName id="4C2734EBFFA4FF8FFECCFD4C6EF81DB4" authorityName="Jussieu" authorityYear="1824" box="[271,430,704,729]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Microstachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B953937AFFA4FF8FFECCFD4C6EF81DB4" box="[271,430,704,729]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="24">Microstachys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of some unusual characters. Study of the 
<typeStatus id="549CF1CAFFA4FF8FFBC8FD4C6B681DB7" box="[1035,1086,704,730]" pageId="6" pageNumber="24">type</typeStatus>
showed, however, that it is a species which is unusual for its long petioles and stipules and for being completely glabrous, but has flowers and fruits typical for 
<taxonomicName id="4C2734EBFFA4FF8FFE4DFC816D7D1C4B" authorityName="Jussieu" authorityYear="1824" box="[398,555,781,806]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Microstachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B953937AFFA4FF8FFE4DFC816D7D1C4B" box="[398,555,781,806]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="24">Microstachys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B984F68FFA4FF8FFF05FCB86A171C85" blockId="6.[151,1437,356,1310]" pageId="6" pageNumber="24">
Pax &amp; Hofmann (1912) and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB63299FFA4FF8FFDDFFCB86C771C23" author="Govaerts, R. &amp; Frodin, D. G. &amp; Radcliffe-Smith, A." box="[540,801,820,846]" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" pagination="1450 - 1464" refId="ref4412" refString="Govaerts, R., Frodin, D. G. &amp; Radcliffe-Smith, A. (2000) Microstachys, Sebastiania. In: World Checklist and Bibliography of Euphorbiaceae (and Pandaceae). Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew, pp. 1183 - 1193, 1450 - 1464." type="journal article" year="2000">
Govaerts 
<emphasis id="B953937AFFA4FF8FFD4CFCB86D9D1C20" box="[655,715,820,845]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="24">et al.</emphasis>
(2000)
</bibRefCitation>
listed the name ' 
<taxonomicName id="4C2734EBFFA4FF8FFC2EFCB86E521C19" authority="(Mull. Arg.) Klotzsch" authorityName="Klotzsch" baseAuthorityName="Mull. Arg." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Microstachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stipulacea">
<emphasis id="B953937AFFA4FF8FFC2EFCB86A5D1C20" box="[1005,1291,820,845]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="24">Microstachys stipulacea</emphasis>
(Müll.Arg.) Klotzsch
</taxonomicName>
ex Baillon' as a synonym under 
<taxonomicName id="4C2734EBFFA4FF8FFD5FFCD66CE41C1E" authorityName="Muller (1866:" authorityYear="1176" baseAuthorityName="Mull. Arg." box="[668,946,858,883]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Sebastiania" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stipulacea">
<emphasis id="B953937AFFA4FF8FFD5FFCD66CE41C1E" box="[668,946,858,883]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="24">Sebastiania stipulacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. That name was however never validly published. The herbarium name of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2734EBFFA4FF8FFD97FC0D6CD31CF7" box="[596,901,897,922]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Microstachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stipulacea">
<emphasis id="B953937AFFA4FF8FFD97FC0D6CD31CF7" box="[596,901,897,922]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="24">Microstachys stipulacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of Klotzsch (who died 1860) predates the publication of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB63299FFA4FF8FFE89FC246EAE1CAF" author="Muller, J." box="[330,504,936,962]" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" pagination="1 - 126" refId="ref4655" refString="Muller, J. (1863) Vorlaufige Mitteilungen aus dem fur De Candolle's Prodromus bestimmten Manuscript uber diese Familie. Linnaea 32: 1 - 126." type="journal article" year="1863">Müller (1863)</bibRefCitation>
, but was only cited as synonym by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB63299FFA4FF8FFC6DFC246B321CAF" author="Baillon, H." box="[942,1124,936,962]" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" pagination="305 - 360" refId="ref4191" refString="Baillon, H. (1865) Species Euphorbiacearum: Euphorbiacees Americaines. Adansonia 5: 305 - 360." type="journal article" year="1865">Baillon (1865)</bibRefCitation>
. Both Baillon and Müller treated the species under different genera and did not accept the original herbarium name of Klotzsch.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B984F68FFA4FF8FFF05FC796DF81BBD" blockId="6.[151,1437,356,1310]" pageId="6" pageNumber="24">
The original type collection (
<emphasis id="B953937AFFA4FF8FFDDAFC796DFE1B63" box="[537,680,1013,1038]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="24">Sellow 3456</emphasis>
, B) was labelled as being collected in ‘Brasil’, and as such, cited for 
<collectingCountry id="F3300FF8FFA4FF8FFF03FB906E511B5B" box="[192,263,1052,1078]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="24">Brazil</collectingCountry>
by e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB63299FFA4FF8FFEAEFB906DC61B5B" author="Pax, F. &amp; Hoffmann, K." box="[365,656,1052,1078]" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" pagination="52" refId="ref4728" refString="Pax, F. &amp; Hoffmann, K. (1912) Euphorbiaceae-Hippomaneae. In: Engler, A. (ed.), Das Pflanzenreich IV, 147, V (Heft 52). Engelmann, Leipzig." type="book chapter" year="1912">Pax &amp; Hoffmann (1912)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB63299FFA4FF8FFD58FB906C6C1B5B" author="Urban, I." box="[667,826,1052,1078]" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" pagination="177 - 198" refId="ref4823" refString="Urban, I. (1893) Biographische Skizzen: Friedrich Sellow (1789 - 1831). Botanische Jahrbucher 17: 177 - 198." type="journal article" year="1893">Urban (1893)</bibRefCitation>
showed, however, that Sellow’s collection numbers 3331–3623 were collected while travelling from southernmost 
<collectingCountry id="F3300FF8FFA4FF8FFC5CFBCE6CBF1B31" box="[927,1001,1090,1116]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="24">Brazil</collectingCountry>
into northern 
<collectingCountry id="F3300FF8FFA4FF8FFB58FBCE6A531B31" box="[1179,1285,1090,1116]" name="Uruguay" pageId="6" pageNumber="24">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
and back to Alegrete. Therefore the type locality is uncertain. The 
<typeStatus id="549CF1CAFFA4FF8FFCEBFBE56CC61BEE" box="[808,912,1129,1155]" pageId="6" pageNumber="24">holotype</typeStatus>
is lost. There are 
<specimenCount id="9D2184E1FFA4FF8FFBA8FBE56B851BEE" box="[1131,1235,1129,1155]" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" type="generic">two type</specimenCount>
sheets in G. The 
<typeStatus id="549CF1CAFFA4FF8FFF54FB1C6E541BC7" box="[151,258,1168,1194]" pageId="6" pageNumber="24">lectotype</typeStatus>
chosen here is a poor specimen but with original annotations by Müller. The isolectotype is a better collection, but without original labels (fig. 3).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
